    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Medium model risk. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is partially compensated by the parametric sensitivity sweep, which demonstrates that QoI predictions remain within acceptance bounds across the plausible input space. The computational sensitivity analysis is considered to provide evidence of equivalent informational value to additional experimental replication under varied conditions, supporting an overall Accepted determination.",
